Given $\{a_n\}_{n=0}^\infty$ and $\{b_n\}_{n=0}^\infty$ bounded sequences; show that if $\lim \limits_{n\to \infty}a_n-b_n=0$ then both sequences have the same subsequential limits. My attempt to prove this begins with: Let $E_A=\{L|L$ subsequential limit of $a_n$}
and $E_B=\{L|L$ subsequential limit of $b_n$}. We need to show that $E_A=E_B$. Given bounded sequence $a_n$ and $b_n$ we know from B.W that each sequence has a subsequence that converges, therefore both $E_A$ and $E_B$ are not empty; Let $L\in E_A$. 
How can I show that $L\in E_B$? Thank you very much.
